<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="59" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">
6. 
<taxonomicName LSID="25B9446A-F51A-08CA-D44C-33C2AA4ABCA7" authority="(Adams, 1817)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Adams" baseAuthorityYear="1817" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera fischeri" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fischeri">Calomera fischeri (Adams, 1817)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="59" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">
On river banks and next to freshwater ponds with sparse vegetation on sandy, sometimes cohesive soil (
<bibRefCitation author="Arndt, E" editor="Arndt, E" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia" pageId="38" pageNumber="81" pagination="73 - 76" refId="B8" refString="Arndt, E, 2011. Tribe Cicindelini Latreille, 1802. In: Arndt, E, Schnitter, P, Sfenthourakis, S, Wrase, DW, Eds., Ground beetles (Carabidae) of Greece. Pensoft, Sofia: 73 - 76" title="Tribe Cicindelini Latreille, 1802." volumeTitle="Ground beetles (Carabidae) of Greece." year="2011">Arndt 2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Avgin, SS" journalOrPublisher="BAUE Fen Bil Enst Degisi" pageId="38" pageNumber="81" pagination="23 - 28" refId="B14" refString="Avgin, SS, 2006. General information and tiger beetles Cicindela herbacea; Calomera fischeri fischeri and Homodela ismenia kilikiensis collected from southeast of Turkey (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). BAUE Fen Bil Enst Degisi 8: 23 - 28" title="General information and tiger beetles Cicindela herbacea; Calomera fischeri fischeri and Homodela ismenia kilikiensis collected from southeast of Turkey (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." volume="8" year="2006">Avgin 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Werner, K" journalOrPublisher="Science Nat, Venette" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" refId="B110" refString="Werner, K, 1992. Cicindelidae 2. Science Nat, Venette" title="Cicindelidae 2." year="1992">Werner 1992</bibRefCitation>
). In desert habitats the species can be widespread (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wiesner, J" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="45" pageNumber="88" pagination="382 - 384" refId="B115" refString="Wiesner, J, 1996. Weitere Mitteilungen ueber die Cicindelidae (Coleoptera) der Vereinigten Arabischen Emirate. Entomologische Zeitschrift 106: 382 - 384" title="Weitere Mitteilungen ueber die Cicindelidae (Coleoptera) der Vereinigten Arabischen Emirate." volume="106" year="1996">Wiesner 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Diurnal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="59" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">
In Turkey, adults from the end of May to the beginning of September (
<bibRefCitation author="Avgin, SS" journalOrPublisher="BAUE Fen Bil Enst Degisi" pageId="38" pageNumber="81" pagination="23 - 28" refId="B14" refString="Avgin, SS, 2006. General information and tiger beetles Cicindela herbacea; Calomera fischeri fischeri and Homodela ismenia kilikiensis collected from southeast of Turkey (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). BAUE Fen Bil Enst Degisi 8: 23 - 28" title="General information and tiger beetles Cicindela herbacea; Calomera fischeri fischeri and Homodela ismenia kilikiensis collected from southeast of Turkey (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." volume="8" year="2006">Avgin 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">Distribution range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">
from southeastern Europe to central Asia and India, southwards to Turkey and Syria (
<bibRefCitation author="Acciavatti, RE" journalOrPublisher="Annales of Carnegie Museum" pageId="38" pageNumber="81" pagination="77 - 353" refId="B4" refString="Acciavatti, RE, Pearson, DL, 1989. The tiger beetle genus Cicindela (Coleoptera, Insecta) from the Indian subcontinent. Annales of Carnegie Museum 58: 77 - 353" title="The tiger beetle genus Cicindela (Coleoptera, Insecta) from the Indian subcontinent." volume="58" year="1989">Acciavatti and Pearson 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Werner, K" journalOrPublisher="Science Nat, Venette" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" refId="B109" refString="Werner, K, 1991. Cicindelidae 1. Science Nat, Venette" title="Cicindelidae 1." year="1991">Werner 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wiesner, J" journalOrPublisher="Erna Bauer, Keltern" pageId="45" pageNumber="88" refId="B114" refString="Wiesner, J, 1992. Checklist of the tiger beetles of the world. Erna Bauer, Keltern" title="Checklist of the tiger beetles of the world." year="1992">Wiesner 1992</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Austin, K" journalOrPublisher="Annales du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle de Nice" pageId="38" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 199" refId="B13" refString="Austin, K, Small, E, Lemaire, J-M, Jeanne, C, Makris, C, Georghiou, G, 2008. Revision du Catalogue des Carabidae (Coleoptera) de Chypre. A revised catalogue of the Carabidae (Coleoptera) of Cyprus. Annales du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle de Nice 23: 1 - 199" title="Revision du Catalogue des Carabidae (Coleoptera) de Chypre. A revised catalogue of the Carabidae (Coleoptera) of Cyprus." volume="23" year="2008">Austin et al. (2008</bibRefCitation>
: 22) questioned the occurrence on Cyprus. However, Horn and Roeschkle (1891) list the species for Cyprus, and old records exist in SDEI: &lt;Cyprus, Baudi&gt; (3 specimens in the collections of Kraatz and Rottenberg, Lutz Behne, pers. com.) Therefore, the species is listed correctly by 
<bibRefCitation author="Putchkov, AV" editor="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="99 - 118" refId="B94" refString="Putchkov, AV, Matalin, AV, 2003. Subfamily Cicindelinae. In: Loebl, I, Smetana, A, Eds., Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 99 - 118" title="Subfamily Cicindelinae." volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2003">Putchkov and Matalin (2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Putchkov, AV" editor="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="217 - 249" refId="B95" refString="Putchkov, AV, Matalin, AV, 2017. Subfamily Cicindelinae. In: Loebl, I, Loebl, D, Eds., Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 217 - 249" title="Subfamily Cicindelinae." volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
: 219) for Cyprus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">Distribution in the southern Levant.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">
The distribution range of the species in the Middle East seems to be incorrectly reported. Despite the fact that numerous authors mention the species from Israel (
<bibRefCitation author="Avgin, SS" journalOrPublisher="BAUE Fen Bil Enst Degisi" pageId="38" pageNumber="81" pagination="23 - 28" refId="B14" refString="Avgin, SS, 2006. General information and tiger beetles Cicindela herbacea; Calomera fischeri fischeri and Homodela ismenia kilikiensis collected from southeast of Turkey (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). BAUE Fen Bil Enst Degisi 8: 23 - 28" title="General information and tiger beetles Cicindela herbacea; Calomera fischeri fischeri and Homodela ismenia kilikiensis collected from southeast of Turkey (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." volume="8" year="2006">Avgin 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Putchkov, AV" editor="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="99 - 118" refId="B94" refString="Putchkov, AV, Matalin, AV, 2003. Subfamily Cicindelinae. In: Loebl, I, Smetana, A, Eds., Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 99 - 118" title="Subfamily Cicindelinae." volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2003">Putchkov and Matalin 2003</bibRefCitation>
), we do not know of any verified record from the country. There are no specimens in SMNHTAU, and the species is mentioned neither by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nussbaum, Y" journalOrPublisher="YES Quarterly" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="7 - 15" refId="B87" refString="Nussbaum, Y, 1987. Tiger beetles of Israel and Sinai (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). YES Quarterly 4: 7 - 15" title="Tiger beetles of Israel and Sinai (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." volume="4" year="1987">Nussbaum (1987)</bibRefCitation>
nor by 
<bibRefCitation author="Valdenberg, A" journalOrPublisher="Shappirit - Journal of the Israel Entomology Center" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="38 - 48" refId="B105" refString="Valdenberg, A, 1983. The tiger beetles family. General survey of the family and key to species in Israel and Sinai (in Hebrew). Shappirit - Journal of the Israel Entomology Center 1: 38 - 48" title="The tiger beetles family. General survey of the family and key to species in Israel and Sinai (in Hebrew)." volume="1" year="1983">Valdenberg (1983)</bibRefCitation>
. No verifiable records are known from Jordan (Putchkov pers. comm.). However, the species is still listed for Jordan in the latest version of the Palaearctic Catalogue of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1862" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Putchkov, AV" editor="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="217 - 249" refId="B95" refString="Putchkov, AV, Matalin, AV, 2017. Subfamily Cicindelinae. In: Loebl, I, Loebl, D, Eds., Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 217 - 249" title="Subfamily Cicindelinae." volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2017">Putchkov and Matalin 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">
In Israel and Jordan, the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
typical habitats, such as river banks in dynamic floodplains or wet pioneer vegetation with patches of bare ground, have mostly been destroyed or are strongly influenced by human activity. Therefore, a recent occurrence of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. fischeri" pageId="16" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="fischeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="59">C. fischeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Mediterranean part of the southern Levant is unlikely. There is a small chance that the species can be found in wadis or close to water reservoirs in the desert regions (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wiesner, J" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="45" pageNumber="88" pagination="382 - 384" refId="B115" refString="Wiesner, J, 1996. Weitere Mitteilungen ueber die Cicindelidae (Coleoptera) der Vereinigten Arabischen Emirate. Entomologische Zeitschrift 106: 382 - 384" title="Weitere Mitteilungen ueber die Cicindelidae (Coleoptera) der Vereinigten Arabischen Emirate." volume="106" year="1996">Wiesner 1996</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="59" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="59">
The nominate subspecies occurs in the northern Levant, while the subspecies 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera fischeri subsp. elongatosignata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="fischeri" subSpecies="elongatosignata">Calomera fischeri elongatosignata</taxonomicName>
(W. Horn, 1922) is found on the Arabian Peninsula (
<bibRefCitation author="Wiesner, J" journalOrPublisher="Erna Bauer, Keltern" pageId="45" pageNumber="88" refId="B114" refString="Wiesner, J, 1992. Checklist of the tiger beetles of the world. Erna Bauer, Keltern" title="Checklist of the tiger beetles of the world." year="1992">Wiesner 1992</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
